tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.9%), suggesting possible prediabetes, and a significantly increased platelet distribution width, which may indicate platelet size variability but is of unclear clinical significance without further context. Other parameters, including renal function, electrolytes, and blood counts, are unremarkable. Correlation with clinical findings is recommended.
